## 6. PRIVACY AND DATA PROTECTION

### 6.1 GDPR Compliance (European Union)

ATLAS Pro is fully compliant with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):

- **Data Minimization:** The Software collects only aggregate traffic data; no personal data is collected
- **Purpose Limitation:** Data is used only for traffic optimization and system improvement
- **Storage Limitation:** Data retention is configurable (default 1 year)
- **Data Subject Rights:** EU residents may request data access, deletion, or portability
- **Data Processing Agreement:** Available for organizations requiring a signed DPA
- **Breach Notification:** Security incidents are reported within 72 hours as required by GDPR

### 6.2 CCPA Compliance (California)

ATLAS Pro complies with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):

- **Privacy Notice:** Clear information about data collection and use
- **Opt-Out Rights:** Users may opt out of data collection for product improvement
- **Access Rights:** You may request access to all data collected about you
- **Deletion Rights:** You may request deletion of your data (subject to legal holds)
- **Non-Discrimination:** Opt-out rights are provided without discrimination

### 6.3 Data Retention

- **Default Retention Period:** 1 year of historical traffic data
- **Extended Retention:** Audit logs retained for 5 years (recommended)
- **Automatic Deletion:** Old data is automatically deleted according to retention policy
- **Manual Deletion:** You may request deletion at any time (30-day grace period for compliance)
- **Backup Retention:** Archived backups may be retained longer for disaster recovery

### 6.4 No Vehicle Tracking or Surveillance

The Software specifically does NOT:
- ❌ Track individual vehicles or identify vehicle owners
- ❌ Collect personally identifiable information (PII)
- ❌ Enable mass surveillance or real-time individual tracking
- ❌ Integrate with facial recognition systems
- ❌ Collect video footage of individuals
- ❌ Use license plate recognition for surveillance purposes

The Software collects only aggregate traffic flow metrics (number of vehicles, average speed, occupancy) — not individual vehicle data.

