## 8. TERMINATION

### 8.1 Termination for Convenience

- **SaaS Subscriptions:** You may terminate your subscription at any time with 30 days' written notice. Termination is effective at the end of the current billing period
- **Perpetual Licenses:** Perpetual licenses do not have a termination right; you may continue using your licensed version indefinitely (subject to Section 8.3)

### 8.2 Termination for Cause

Licensor may immediately terminate your license if you:
- Violate material terms of this Agreement
- Fail to pay required fees (after 15 days' written notice)
- Exceed your licensed capacity without authorization
- Use the Software for unlawful or unauthorized purposes
- Attempt to reverse engineer or circumvent security features
- Breach confidentiality obligations

### 8.3 Effect of Termination

Upon termination of your license:
- Your right to use the Software immediately ceases
- You must uninstall and cease all use of the Software
- You may export your data in standard formats for 30 days after termination
- Sections 2-7 (Intellectual Property, Liability, Privacy, Security) survive termination indefinitely
- You are responsible for fees accrued through the termination date

### 8.4 Survival

The following provisions survive termination: Intellectual Property (Section 2), Limitations of Liability (Section 5), Privacy (Section 6), Export Compliance (Section 7.4), and Governing Law (Section 9).

